AUDIO: 'And this is where Lance hands us the most useful framework in the whole post. Using memory well is a ladder with five rungs. Rung one, fail. Get something wrong and write it down. Rung two, investigate.'

[09:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Before moving on, figure out why. Rung three, verify. Turn the diagnosis into a checked fact. Rung four,'

[09:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'distill. Turn the fact into a general rule. rung five consult Next session, read the rule instead of re-deriving it. Now, watch where each model gets off the'

[09:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ladder. Sonnet 4.6 exits at rung one. Its memory is a pile of failure notes and open guesses. Maybe the price column has a different name, {question mark}'

[09:57] [scene:talk]
